[git works better with linux]

0. at any time, to see the git settings
	$ git config -l

1. removing the old origin
	$ git remote rm origin

2. adding current working origin
	$ git remote add origin https://github.com/TheCoApp/Talbish

3. change path to the desired working path, you must not be inside an older folder of the git repository

4. get the repositery
	$ git clone https://github.com/TheCoApp/Talbish

...work

5. if nedded, add the new files and directories
	$ git add

6. from inside the working directory, commit your work to the git log. write exactly what have you done, so anyone can understand without calling you in 2:00 AM
	$ git commit

7. push your changes to the repository
	$ git push
